=== Key Capabilities
<key-capabilities>
The NeqSim capabilities most relevant to this book are:

- #strong[Equation of state library] --- SRK, PR (both with volume translation), CPA (for polar systems like water, methanol, MEG), Electrolyte CPA (for brine chemistry and scale prediction), GERG-2008 (custody transfer reference for natural gas), PC-SAFT, and UMR-PRU
- #strong[Flash calculations] --- TP flash, PH flash, PS flash, TV flash, bubble point and dew point calculations, hydrate equilibrium temperature and pressure
- #strong[Transport properties] --- viscosity (LBC, PFCT, corresponding states), thermal conductivity, surface tension, and diffusion coefficients for all phases
- #strong[Process equipment] --- streams, separators (2-phase, 3-phase), compressors (with performance curves), heat exchangers (shell-and-tube, plate), valves (Cv-based), pipes (Beggs and Brill), mixers, splitters, distillation columns, absorbers, reactors
- #strong[Dynamic simulation] --- transient equipment models with PID controllers, transmitters (PT, TT, LT, FT), and alarm logic
- #strong[Multiphase pipe flow] --- Beggs and Brill correlation with pipeline elevation profile and heat transfer to surroundings
- #strong[Reservoir models] --- simple reservoir with drive mechanism and decline, suitable for integrated production modeling

=== The NeqSim Ecosystem
<the-neqsim-ecosystem>
NeqSim operates as an ecosystem of interconnected components:

- #strong[Java core] (`neqsim-*.jar`) --- the main library, containing all thermodynamic and process simulation classes. Can be used directly from Java applications or any JVM-compatible language.
- #strong[Python interface] (`pip install neqsim`) --- uses jpype to bridge Python and the Java core, enabling use from Jupyter notebooks, scripts, and automation systems. All Java classes are accessible from Python with automatic type conversion.
- #strong[Jupyter notebooks] --- the primary working environment for this book. Each chapter includes companion notebooks with runnable code examples that can be executed, modified, and extended.
- #strong[MCP server] --- a Model Context Protocol server that exposes NeqSim calculations as web services, enabling integration with AI assistants, web applications, and external optimization engines.
- #strong[Automation API] --- the `ProcessAutomation` class provides string-addressable access to all simulation variables, designed for programmatic access from optimization algorithms, digital twin systems, and real-time advisory tools.

