=== Corrosion Allowance and Material Selection
<corrosion-allowance-and-material-selection>
The corrosion allowance is the extra wall thickness added to account for metal loss over the design life:

$ C A = C R times t_(d e s i g n) $

For a typical 25-year design life with $C R = 0.3$ mm/year: $C A = 7.5$ mm. If the corrosion rate exceeds approximately 0.3 mm/year with inhibition, corrosion-resistant alloys (CRAs) are typically selected:

