== Oil Export Quality and Specifications
<oil-export-quality-and-specifications>
=== Comprehensive Export Quality Parameters
<comprehensive-export-quality-parameters>
Beyond vapor pressure and water content, crude oil quality is characterized by several parameters that affect its market value:

- #strong[API gravity]: Measures the oil density relative to water. Light crudes (\>35° API) command premium prices; heavy crudes (\<25° API) are discounted.

$ upright("API") = 141.5 / upright("SG")_(60 degree F) - 131.5 $

- #strong[Sulfur content]: Sweet crudes (\<0.5 wt% S) trade at a premium over sour crudes (\>1.5 wt% S)
- #strong[TAN (Total Acid Number)]: High-TAN crudes (\>0.5 mg KOH/g) cause naphthenic acid corrosion
- #strong[Wax content]: Affects pour point and pumpability
- #strong[Asphaltene content]: Affects stability and emulsion tendency
- #strong[Pour point]: The lowest temperature at which the crude flows under standard conditions; critical for pipeline transport in cold climates
- #strong[Viscosity]: Affects pipeline transport, pumping requirements, and processing performance
- #strong[Density (specific gravity)]: Used for custody transfer volume calculations

