== Summary
<summary>
This chapter has covered the major gas processing operations required to convert raw natural gas into pipeline-quality sales gas and valuable NGL products:

+ #strong[TEG dehydration] is the standard method for water dew point control, with enhanced regeneration (stripping gas, Stahl column, Drizo) extending the achievable dew point depression below −40°C.
+ #strong[Hydrocarbon dew point control] can be achieved through JT cooling (simple, low CAPEX), turboexpander (efficient, work recovery), or mechanical refrigeration (independent of pressure drop).
+ #strong[NGL recovery] using turboexpander processes with demethanizer columns can achieve ethane recovery above 90% with modern enhanced processes.
+ #strong[Acid gas removal] using amine treating is the standard for H$""_2$S and CO$""_2$ removal, with MDEA offering selective H$""_2$S removal and lower regeneration energy.
+ #strong[NeqSim provides] comprehensive modeling capability for all these unit operations, with the CPA equation of state being particularly important for accurate water--glycol--hydrocarbon equilibria in dehydration calculations.
+ The #strong[integration] of these processing steps requires careful attention to heat and pressure management to minimize energy consumption and maximize product recovery.

