== Seawater Cooling Systems
<seawater-cooling-systems>
=== Design Considerations
<design-considerations>
Seawater is the primary cooling medium for most offshore platforms. Design considerations include:

- #strong[Corrosion] --- seawater is highly corrosive; titanium or Cu-Ni tubes are typically required
- #strong[Biofouling] --- marine organisms colonize surfaces; chlorination or anti-fouling coatings are needed
- #strong[Temperature variation] --- seawater temperature varies seasonally from 2 °C (Arctic) to 32 °C (Gulf)
- #strong[Environmental regulations] --- maximum discharge temperature rise (typically 7 °C above ambient)
- #strong[Intake depth] --- deeper intake provides colder, cleaner water

=== Material Selection
<material-selection>
