The analysis shows that the HP Compressor is the first bottleneck, and a driver uprate combined with adding a cyclone inlet device to the HP Separator would provide the largest production gain per unit investment.

=== Recommended Debottlenecking Sequence
<recommended-debottlenecking-sequence>
Based on the NPV analysis:

+ #strong[Phase 1] (Year 1): Add cyclone inlet to HP Separator (PI = 12.3) and drag reduction agent for export pipeline (PI = 15.8). Low cost, high return.
+ #strong[Phase 2] (Year 2): Uprate HP Compressor driver (PI = 7.2). Requires shutdown for installation.
+ #strong[Phase 3] (Year 3): Add 3rd hydrocyclone (PI = 4.8). Only needed if water cut continues to rise.
+ #strong[Phase 4] (Contingency): VSD on LP Compressor (PI = 3.5). Reserve for late-life gas lift requirements.

Total investment: 90 MNOK for Phases 1-2. Expected production gain: 12,500 bbl/d.~Payback period: 4 months at \$70/bbl.

