== Mathematical Summary
<mathematical-summary>
=== The Production Optimization Problem
<the-production-optimization-problem>
The complete mathematical formulation of the NeqSim production optimization problem is:

$ max_x quad f \( x \) = sum_(j = 1)^k w_j dot.op hat(f)_j \( x \) $

subject to:

#strong[Equipment capacity constraints (from CapacityConstrainedEquipment):]

$ U_i \( x \) lt.eq U_(i \, upright("limit")) quad forall i in cal(E) $

#strong[Hard process constraints:]

$ g_m \( x \) lt.eq 0 quad forall m in cal(H) $

#strong[Soft process constraints (penalized):]

$ f_(upright("penalized")) \( x \) = f \( x \) - sum_(m in cal(S)) lambda_m dot.op max \( 0 \, g_m \( x \) \) $

#strong[Bound constraints:]

$ x^L lt.eq x lt.eq x^U $

where: - $x$ is the vector of decision variables (flow rates, pressures, temperatures) - $f_j \( x \)$ are the objective functions (production rate, power, quality) - $w_j$ are objective weights - $U_i \( x \)$ is the utilization of equipment $i$ - $U_(i \, upright("limit"))$ is the utilization limit for equipment $i$ - $cal(E)$ is the set of capacity-constrained equipment - $cal(H)$ is the set of hard constraints - $cal(S)$ is the set of soft constraints - $lambda_m$ is the penalty weight for soft constraint $m$

=== Composite Score Function
<composite-score-function>
The optimizer evaluates candidates using a composite score:

$ S \( x \) = cases(delim: "{", sum_j w_j hat(f)_j \( x \) & upright("if feasible (all ") U_i lt.eq U_(i \, upright("limit")) upright(" and all hard constraints OK)"), sum_j w_j hat(f)_j \( x \) - sum_m lambda_m max \( 0 \, g_m \( x \) \) - Lambda sum_i max \( 0 \, U_i - U_(i \, upright("limit")) \) & upright("if infeasible")) $

where $Lambda$ is a large penalty weight that ensures feasible solutions always score higher than infeasible ones.

