The optimized total oil production is 18,800 Sm³/d --- a 20% reduction from the unconstrained sum, but this is the maximum achievable within facility limits. Attempting to produce 23,500 Sm³/d would violate both the gas handling and water treatment constraints.

=== Sensitivity Analysis
<sensitivity-analysis>
The case study reveals important sensitivities:

#strong[Gas handling capacity expansion:] Increasing gas handling by 10% (to 3,850,000 Sm³/d) allows an additional 1,200 Sm³/d of oil production --- primarily by relaxing the choke on Wells P-3 and P-2.

#strong[Separator pressure reduction:] Reducing separator pressure from 65 to 55 bara increases total oil by approximately 800 Sm³/d by improving well deliverability across all wells.

#strong[Well P-5 shut-in:] Shutting in Well P-5 and redistributing its gas capacity to other wells produces almost the same total oil with significantly less water to treat. This may be the preferred strategy when water treatment is the binding constraint.

