=== Automatic Interpolation
<automatic-interpolation>
The reservoir simulator interpolates across all four VFP dimensions at each timestep:

$ P_(B H P) = f \( Q \, P_(T H P) \, upright("WC") \( t \) \, upright("GOR") \( t \) \) $

where $upright("WC") \( t \)$ and $upright("GOR") \( t \)$ change with time as the reservoir depletes. Multi-linear interpolation is used:

$ P_(B H P) approx sum_(i \, j \, k \, l) w_(i j k l) dot.op P_(B H P)^(\( i \, j \, k \, l \)) $

where $w_(i j k l)$ are the interpolation weights determined by the current well conditions relative to the table grid points.

This means the VFP table must have sufficient resolution in each dimension to avoid interpolation errors:

#figure(
  align(center)[#table(
    columns: 4,
    align: (auto,auto,auto,auto,),
    table.header([Dimension], [Minimum Points], [Recommended Points], [Rationale],),
    table.hline(),
    [Flow rate], [5], [8--10], [Non-linear friction],
    [THP], [3], [5--6], [Linear-ish behavior],
    [Water cut], [4], [5--6], [Non-linear density/viscosity],
    [GOR], [4], [6--8], [Highly non-linear phase behavior],
  )]
  , kind: table
  )

=== WCONPROD Well Control
<wconprod-well-control>
The `WCONPROD` keyword specifies well operating mode and constraints. The VFP table number links each well to its performance model:

- #strong[ORAT mode:] Target oil rate, BHP from VFP table
- #strong[GRAT mode:] Target gas rate
- #strong[LRAT mode:] Target liquid rate (oil + water)
- #strong[RESV mode:] Target reservoir voidage rate
- #strong[BHP mode:] Fixed bottomhole pressure (VFP gives achievable rate)

