The simulation reveals several important features:

+ #strong[Level response]: When the feed rate increases by 60% at $t = 10$ min, the level rises because liquid enters faster than it leaves. The level controller responds by opening the liquid valve, gradually returning the level to the set point. The integral action eliminates the offset.
+ #strong[Pressure response]: The increased gas flow causes a temporary pressure rise, which the pressure controller handles by opening the gas valve.
+ #strong[Return to steady state]: After the disturbance is removed at $t = 20$ min, both controllers bring the process back to the set point. The level controller overshoot and settling time depend on the tuning parameters.

