  )

=== Bias Updating
<bias-updating>
A simpler alternative to full parameter estimation is #strong[bias updating] --- adding a constant correction to each model output to match the measurement:

$ y_(upright("corrected"))^(upright("model")) = y^(upright("model")) + b $

where the bias $b = y^(upright("measured")) - y^(upright("model"))$ is updated at each calibration cycle. This is fast and robust but does not improve the model's ability to predict behavior at different operating conditions.

