#strong[Real-Time Optimization] closes the loop between process models and plant operations by continuously re-optimizing set points as conditions change. An RTO system executes the following cycle:

=== The RTO Cycle
<the-rto-cycle>
The RTO cycle runs every 15--60 minutes:

+ #strong[Data collection]: Read current measurements from the plant historian
+ #strong[Steady-state detection]: Confirm the plant is at steady state using R-statistic or similar methods (Section 22.5.1)
+ #strong[Data reconciliation]: Reconcile measurements to satisfy mass/energy balances (Section 22.5.2)
+ #strong[Parameter estimation]: Update key model parameters (efficiency, fouling factors, etc.) to match current conditions (Section 22.5.4)
+ #strong[Optimization]: Solve the optimization problem using the calibrated model
+ #strong[Implementation]: Send optimized set points to the DCS/APC layer

