== Synthesis --- Common Themes Across Case Studies
<synthesis-common-themes-across-case-studies>
The three case studies, despite covering very different systems (offshore gas condensate platform, FPSO heavy oil, onshore gas plant), share several common themes that apply broadly to production optimization:

=== Integrated Modeling Is Essential
<integrated-modeling-is-essential>
No piece of equipment operates in isolation. Changing the HP separator pressure on the gas condensate platform (Case 1) affects condensate recovery, gas compression power, and export pipeline hydraulics simultaneously. Building an integrated model captures these interactions.

=== Bottlenecks Shift Over Time
<bottlenecks-shift-over-time>
The bottleneck equipment changes as production conditions evolve: - #strong[Case 1]: Export compressor is the bottleneck at current rates - #strong[Case 2]: 1st stage separator liquid handling becomes the bottleneck as water cut rises - #strong[Case 3]: Amine absorber is the bottleneck for throughput increase

Systematic capacity checks (Chapter 18) should be performed regularly, not just at design stage.

=== Optimization Is Multi-Objective
<optimization-is-multi-objective>
Production optimization rarely has a single objective. The real trade-offs are: - #strong[Case 1]: Condensate recovery vs compression power (revenue vs cost) - #strong[Case 2]: Oil production vs water handling capacity (production vs CAPEX) - #strong[Case 3]: NGL recovery vs throughput (product value vs capacity)

The economic objective function must balance all these factors.

=== Sensitivity Analysis Reveals Risk
<sensitivity-analysis-reveals-risk>
Parametric studies --- varying water cut (Case 2), separator pressure (Case 1), or feed rate (Case 3) --- reveal how sensitive the system is to changing conditions. This information is critical for risk assessment and investment decisions.

#horizontalrule

== Summary
<summary>
This chapter presented three integrated case studies that exercise the full range of production optimization techniques covered in this book:

- #strong[Case Study 1] (Offshore Gas Condensate Platform) demonstrated capacity analysis and separator pressure optimization on a complete platform model with wells, separation, recompression, and export compression. The export compressor was identified as the bottleneck, and HP separator pressure optimization provided 5--8% condensate uplift.

- #strong[Case Study 2] (FPSO Heavy Oil Production) analyzed the impact of rising water cut on FPSO performance. The 1st stage separator liquid handling capacity becomes the bottleneck at approximately 65% water cut, and proactive water handling upgrades are recommended before reaching this threshold.

- #strong[Case Study 3] (Onshore Gas Plant Debottlenecking) performed a systematic check of all equipment against design capacities at a 20% throughput increase. The amine absorber was identified as the primary bottleneck, and a phased debottlenecking strategy was recommended with a rapid payback.

All three case studies used NeqSim's `ProcessModel` to build multi-area models and `ProcessAutomation` for programmatic result extraction and optimization.

